{
  "stem": "2435.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we saw that the glass was lying on the street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "People tried to sweep the glass away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were horrified.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we went-- later on, much later-- around 5:00, we went out and we saw the nearby synagogue.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I could not tell you the name of the synagogue, which was owned by [INAUDIBLE] in shatter.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The-- the glass were all-- was all taken out, and on the-- in the yard were the prayer books, torn up, and there were ashes all over.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was a horrible look.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The-- the-- the temple-- the synagogue was hardly recognizable.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And even though Mom, Dad, nor Hans nor I ever went to the synagogue, but what a horrible experience for the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And we only saw that some people were cleaning up the ashes in that-- in that courtyard.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- yeah, I do think they engaged Jewish people, not the Christian, because I have read that some Jewish people later on had to be on their knees cleaning up the-- the glasses and all.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had read that in one of the books.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, when the-- yeah, when the war broke out, of course, we were in the cellar, in the Luftschutzkeller.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was '39.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had already-- every time when we heard the sirens-- and I still, in memory, hear the sirens blowing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a terrible sound.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were always packed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a big suitcase and little bags, which we were supposed to take down with some food and the most necessary things, because we knew that, in the Luftschutzkeller, we had to sit for a long time.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we-- Mum and Dad and I do not remember that Hans was there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That I do not remember.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
